| **Instrumentality / Agency Test**           | *Ajay Hasia v. Khalid Mujib* (1981) distilled six guiding factors to identify a State instrumentality:<br>1. Government share-capital<br>2. Predominant financial assistance<br>3. State-protected monopoly<br>4. Deep & pervasive administrative control<br>5. Public-importance of functions<br>6. Transfer of government department (Shukla; Jain). |
